          <p>üí° <strong>Key Insight:</strong> $100 invested in Bitcoin in 2013 would be worth over $100,000 today. No other liquid asset has delivered comparable returns.</p>
        </div>

        <p>With a hard cap of 21 million coins and decreasing issuance (halving every 4 years), Bitcoin is the scarcest monetary asset ever created. This scarcity, combined with growing institutional adoption, creates a compelling long-term case.</p>
      </div>

